g.aria-label: Besides the calorie-burning effect of strength training, it enhances fat loss due to an improved metabolic efficiency.
Strength training can significantly boost resting metabolic rate (RMR) by 9% - meaning you burn more calories.
Resistance training uses a combination of mechanical tension and metabolic stress to increase muscle hypertrophy.
Resistance training and cardio can increase energy expenditure. Training, besides helping you burn more calories, it makes the body more efficient at creating energy.
